cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SD, cs.NE 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with Natural Language Generation in Spoken Dialogue Systems. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes an adversarial training procedure to train a Variational encoder-decoder based language generator. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with adapting a model to perform acceptably well on a different target domain. 
4. cs.SD (Sound) is a less likely category as the paper does not focus on sound processing, but rather on language generation in spoken dialogue systems. 
5. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a less likely category as the paper does not focus on evolutionary computing, but rather on neural language generation.
